        %h1 Chat real-time
        %p Got questions? Want to discuss an issue in real-time? Then join us on IRC.
        %p Most of our project discussion take place on IRC, usually during European and American daytime.
        %h2 Connection info
        %ul
          %li
            Chat in
            %a{:href => "http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=dashbuillder%2Cdrools&uio=d4", :target => "_blank"} your browser
          %li
            Chat with an IRC client (
            %a{:href => "http://www.xchat.org/", :target => "_blank"} XChat
            (Linux),
            %a{:href => "http://colloquy.info/", :target => "_blank"} Colloquy
            (Mac),
            %a{:href => "http://www.hydrairc.com/", :target => "_blank"} HydraIRC
            (Windows), …):
            %ul
              %li
                IRC server:
                %strong chat.freenode.net:6667
                %ul
                  %li
                    %a{:href => "http://freenode.net/irc_servers.shtml", :target => "_blank"} List of alternative servers
              %li
                Channels for users:
                %ul
                  %li
                    %strong #dashbuilder
              %li
                Channels for contributors:
                %ul
                  %li
                    %strong #dashbuilderdev
        %h2 Guidelines
        %ul
          %li
            Answers can take a while. Wait at least an hour. If no one answers, then they are busy or AFK. Try the
            %a{:href => "forum.html"} forum
            instead.
          %li
            Don’t send private messages to anyone, use only the public channels. Private support is reserved for Red Hat customers only.
          %li
            No need to waste time by asking "Can I ask a question?". Just ask your question immediately.
          %li
            If you need assistance with other JBoss projects, try their IRC channel on Freenode.

